1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:19,052
You're watching <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
with guests Lee Da-hee and DEX.

2
00:00:19,119 --> 00:00:21,654
DEX, you were the legendary catfish.

3
00:00:21,721 --> 00:00:24,657
There's a really famous moment.

4
00:00:25,291 --> 00:00:27,327
There's that great moment.

5
00:00:27,394 --> 00:00:31,097
He didn't bother to celebrate.
He just threw the flag down nonchalantly.

6
00:00:31,164 --> 00:00:34,701
<i>I started in the middle of the show,</i>
<i>so I had to leave a strong impression,</i>

7
00:00:34,768 --> 00:00:36,269
<i>even more than the existing participants.</i>

8
00:00:36,336 --> 00:00:39,539
<i>-It would've been over if I lost there.</i>
<i>-I see.</i>

9
00:00:39,606 --> 00:00:42,642
<i>I had to give everything I had.</i>

10
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:45,612
That moment was the first time
I noticed DEX.

11
00:00:45,678 --> 00:00:46,880
He left an impression

12
00:00:46,946 --> 00:00:48,681
because most people would celebrate

13
00:00:48,748 --> 00:00:52,952
even if they wouldn't want to
because they'd be immersed in the moment.

14
00:00:53,019 --> 00:00:54,988
But he pulled it out,
threw it, and walked off.

15
00:00:55,055 --> 00:00:56,623
I couldn't forget
the expression on his face.

16
00:00:56,689 --> 00:01:01,127
He left the strongest impression
among every male participant

17
00:01:01,194 --> 00:01:03,930
after playing that game.

18
00:01:03,997 --> 00:01:06,900
Chef Hyun-suk does his celebration
right away with his apron.

19
00:01:06,966 --> 00:01:09,235
-He does.
-It's just human nature.

20
00:01:09,302 --> 00:01:12,405
You thought he'd celebrate, but he didn't.

21
00:01:12,472 --> 00:01:14,240
That's why he captured women's hearts.

22
00:01:15,008 --> 00:01:18,478
-But you say you're only popular with men.
-I am.

23
00:01:18,545 --> 00:01:21,848
I have way more male contacts on my phone.

24
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:24,684
-And I tend to like older male friends.
-I see.

25
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:27,353
I think it's because I like sports,

26
00:01:27,420 --> 00:01:30,790
-so I call myself the bro collector.
-The bro collector.

27
00:01:30,857 --> 00:01:33,626
Only Chef Sung-jun is the same age as you,

28
00:01:33,693 --> 00:01:36,329
-and everyone else is older.
-Yes, they are.

29
00:01:36,396 --> 00:01:38,264
Do you want to befriend anyone here?

30
00:01:38,331 --> 00:01:39,532
RADAR ON

31
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:42,402
GULP

32
00:01:43,369 --> 00:01:45,505
Do you want to befriend anyone here?

33
00:01:47,540 --> 00:01:48,541
I found myself

34
00:01:48,608 --> 00:01:51,744
-continuously drawn to Chef Kang-rok.
-I see.

35
00:01:51,811 --> 00:01:53,713
-That's peculiar.
-He's got that magical charm.

36
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:56,583
He doesn't even do much,

37
00:01:56,649 --> 00:02:00,186
-but he intrigues everyone.
-He keeps making me curious.

38
00:02:00,253 --> 00:02:03,690
-"Who is this guy?"
-I want to keep talking to him.

39
00:02:04,324 --> 00:02:05,625
LOOKING AWAY

40
00:02:05,692 --> 00:02:07,560
My goodness.

41
00:02:07,627 --> 00:02:09,596
Can you two…

42
00:02:09,662 --> 00:02:12,065
-Hello.
-Hey.

43
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:13,333
Have you eaten?

44
00:02:14,434 --> 00:02:16,603
-I have. Yes.
-What did you eat?

45
00:02:20,673 --> 00:02:22,475
-What did you eat?
-What did you eat?

46
00:02:22,542 --> 00:02:24,410
Well, no. I haven't eaten.

47
00:02:24,477 --> 00:02:26,146
-Did you lie?
-He lied.

48
00:02:26,212 --> 00:02:28,815
You lied to someone
you've never met before?

49
00:02:28,882 --> 00:02:30,750
I don't like guys who lie.

50
00:02:30,817 --> 00:02:33,052
HE HAS A SOLID TASTE IN FRIENDS

51
00:02:33,119 --> 00:02:35,388
-I take it back.
-You do?

52
00:02:35,455 --> 00:02:37,757
DEX served in the special forces,

53
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:39,325
and he loves sports.

54
00:02:39,392 --> 00:02:41,728
<i>He recently got into mixed martial arts,</i>

55
00:02:41,794 --> 00:02:44,330
<i>gym workouts, and jiujitsu.</i>

56
00:02:44,397 --> 00:02:46,232
<i>-Do you work out every day?</i>
<i>-He must be fit.</i>

57
00:02:46,299 --> 00:02:48,234
I wouldn't say every day.

58
00:02:48,301 --> 00:02:51,905
But I try to go
at least three to four times a week.

59
00:02:51,971 --> 00:02:53,573
-I'm trying.
-That's still a lot.

60
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:55,708
Now that we invited DEX here,

61
00:02:55,775 --> 00:02:57,143
we'll hold a physical match.

62
00:02:57,210 --> 00:02:58,378
A SUDDEN PHYSICAL MATCH

63
00:02:58,444 --> 00:03:00,246
-A physical match? Here?
-We'll do it.

64
00:03:00,313 --> 00:03:03,583
Isn't this a cooking show?
This isn't <i>Physical: 100</i>, is it?

65
00:03:03,650 --> 00:03:06,019
-We like to work out before we eat.
-Is that so?

66
00:03:06,085 --> 00:03:08,288
-It helps you enjoy the food.
-To feel hungry.

67
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:10,223
Let's take DEX down.

68
00:03:10,290 --> 00:03:12,125
It'll be hard to win against him
in a full-on game.

69
00:03:12,192 --> 00:03:17,263
But our chefs have also grown muscles
while working in the kitchen.

70
00:03:17,330 --> 00:03:18,565
It's tough to work in the kitchen.

71
00:03:18,631 --> 00:03:21,267
They especially have
stronger arms than legs.

72
00:03:21,334 --> 00:03:24,837
People say that
chefs have amazing arm strength.

73
00:03:24,904 --> 00:03:27,941
For <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>, Son Jong-won.
Representing <i>Single's Inferno</i>, DEX.

74
00:03:28,007 --> 00:03:30,376
-They'll arm-wrestle.
-Arm-wrestling.

75
00:03:30,443 --> 00:03:33,346
-That's it. Just arm-wrestling.
-That sounds good.

76
00:03:33,413 --> 00:03:35,481
This is a fight over pride for men.

77
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:37,417
-It kills your pride.
-It does.

78
00:03:37,483 --> 00:03:38,985
Chef Jong-won

79
00:03:39,052 --> 00:03:42,021
always works out in the early morning
before he comes to the shoot.

80
00:03:42,088 --> 00:03:43,923
-Really?
-Are you serious?

81
00:03:43,990 --> 00:03:46,025
I do CrossFit.

82
00:03:46,092 --> 00:03:47,360
CrossFit is the real deal.

83
00:03:47,427 --> 00:03:49,495
He's really ripped.

84
00:03:49,562 --> 00:03:51,364
Just arm-wrestling, Chef Jong-won.

85
00:03:52,298 --> 00:03:53,733
THE CATFISH, DEX

86
00:03:54,467 --> 00:03:57,103
-Come on out, Chef Jong-won.
-Okay.

87
00:03:57,170 --> 00:03:58,171
It'll be huge if you win.

88
00:03:58,238 --> 00:03:59,973
If he wins,
will you be Chef Good Vibes' fans?

89
00:04:00,039 --> 00:04:01,374
THEY'LL ADMIT DEFEAT
AND CROSS OVER

90
00:04:01,441 --> 00:04:02,775
-Please grab each other's hands.
-Okay.

91
00:04:02,842 --> 00:04:06,212
We won't lose anything even if we lose.

92
00:04:06,279 --> 00:04:07,914
But if we win, it'll be huge.

93
00:04:07,981 --> 00:04:09,682
The fight has already begun.

94
00:04:09,749 --> 00:04:11,484
Things feel different right here.

95
00:04:11,551 --> 00:04:13,886
I can see their veins popping already.

96
00:04:13,953 --> 00:04:16,222
-Do you see the veins?
-You got this.

97
00:04:16,289 --> 00:04:17,457
-You can do this!
-Get ready.

98
00:04:17,523 --> 00:04:18,891
Stay relaxed right now.

99
00:04:18,958 --> 00:04:21,527
This is a battle over pride for men.

100
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:25,498
Things are feisty here.
They're in high spirits. Ready?

101
00:04:25,565 --> 00:04:28,735
-Chef Jong-won is serious.
-He is.

102
00:04:28,801 --> 00:04:31,571
Let's find out how strong chefs are.

103
00:04:31,638 --> 00:04:33,506
-Get ready.
-You're strong.

104
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:37,710
And go!

105
00:04:43,249 --> 00:04:44,851
And go!

106
00:04:49,155 --> 00:04:50,857
DEX is smiling.

107
00:04:52,492 --> 00:04:53,926
STRUGGLING

108
00:04:55,728 --> 00:04:57,063
-DEX toys around with him.
-No!

109
00:04:57,130 --> 00:04:59,198
My gosh.

110
00:04:59,265 --> 00:05:00,266
THE CATFISH, DEX, WINS

111
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:02,835
-DEX wins.
-He's really strong.

112
00:05:02,902 --> 00:05:05,638
I was so surprised at first
because he was so strong.

113
00:05:06,205 --> 00:05:08,174
THE CATFISH OF CHEF & MY FRIDGE
DID HIS BEST

114
00:05:08,841 --> 00:05:11,010
-I have a feeling…
-I knew it.

115
00:05:11,077 --> 00:05:13,680
-…these two will be stronger.
-That's possible.

116
00:05:13,746 --> 00:05:16,382
-It's their build.
-Because you need shorter arms.

117
00:05:16,449 --> 00:05:17,650
Shorter means a higher chance.

118
00:05:17,717 --> 00:05:19,786
Hey, Sung-jun! Come on out!

119
00:05:19,852 --> 00:05:22,755
-Sung-jun.
-Go, Sung-jun. I know you can do it.

120
00:05:22,822 --> 00:05:23,956
Sung-jun's going to win.

121
00:05:24,023 --> 00:05:25,425
DEX versus <i>Mantecare</i>.

122
00:05:25,491 --> 00:05:26,893
<i>Lastly, it's called</i> mantecare.

123
00:05:26,959 --> 00:05:29,762
<i>It's over ten kilograms</i>
<i>by the time I emulsify it.</i>

124
00:05:29,829 --> 00:05:31,798
-All right, get ready.
-You're in good shape.

125
00:05:31,864 --> 00:05:34,133
MAYBE I DID ALL THAT FOR TODAY

126
00:05:34,701 --> 00:05:35,702
SURPRISED

127
00:05:35,768 --> 00:05:36,936
Oh, my, wait!

128
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:40,773
-Hey, Sung-jun.
-I knew it.

129
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:42,775
-Sung-jun.
-In-between.

130
00:05:42,842 --> 00:05:44,210
He's only a baby on the face.

131
00:05:44,944 --> 00:05:47,580
-His arms are rugged.
-I'm getting sweaty.

132
00:05:47,647 --> 00:05:50,483
Chef Jong-won
sucked the energy out of DEX a bit,

133
00:05:50,550 --> 00:05:52,485
so you can win if you try a little.

134
00:06:02,562 --> 00:06:05,064
-Hey!
-Two seconds.

135
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:08,601
TIME IT TOOK HIM TO LOSE:
2 SECONDS

136
00:06:08,668 --> 00:06:10,503
-Hey, come on!
-Not even two seconds.

137
00:06:10,570 --> 00:06:12,805
-Two seconds.
-Nam-no! Come on out!

138
00:06:12,872 --> 00:06:15,007
-DEX versus Yoon Nam-no.
-Be serious.

139
00:06:19,779 --> 00:06:20,780
SCREAMING

140
00:06:21,914 --> 00:06:22,915
He's different.

141
00:06:22,982 --> 00:06:24,484
We can't win even if we use both hands.

142
00:06:25,184 --> 00:06:27,053
I hear one of the chefs here
served in the Marine Corps.

143
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:28,755
-Former Marine, did you hear that?
-The Marine.

144
00:06:28,821 --> 00:06:30,923
-As someone who served in the UDT…
-That's great.

145
00:06:30,990 --> 00:06:32,325
-Really?
-UDT versus Marine Corps.

146
00:06:32,392 --> 00:06:34,861
-UDT versus Marine Corps.
-Hey, Marine.

147
00:06:34,927 --> 00:06:36,529
-We have a Marine.
-Wait.

148
00:06:36,596 --> 00:06:37,897
Well, you know,

149
00:06:38,631 --> 00:06:39,966
I can't even lift this pen.

150
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:42,835
-But you were a Marine.
-He forfeits.

151
00:06:42,902 --> 00:06:45,071
-He can't even lift that pen.
-Choi Kang-rok.

152
00:06:45,138 --> 00:06:46,172
SHOW US THAT YOU'RE A MARINE,
KANG-ROK!

153
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:48,074
-Go, Kang-rok.
-Okay.

154
00:06:48,141 --> 00:06:49,442
A former Marine.

155
00:06:49,509 --> 00:06:51,411
-There may be a twist.
-I doubt I can do it.

156
00:06:51,477 --> 00:06:53,212
-When did you serve?
-A senior officer.

157
00:06:53,279 --> 00:06:55,114
-I was in the 837th class.
-The 837th class.

158
00:06:55,181 --> 00:06:56,616
-I see.
-Salute!

159
00:06:58,451 --> 00:06:59,752
FEELING SHY

160
00:07:00,987 --> 00:07:01,988
What do you mean by that?

161
00:07:04,056 --> 00:07:05,558
He's saluting. Okay.

162
00:07:05,625 --> 00:07:07,827
-Okay. Get ready.
-Grab him.

163
00:07:07,894 --> 00:07:09,562
I don't think he can do this.

164
00:07:12,031 --> 00:07:13,533
-What?
-What?

165
00:07:14,801 --> 00:07:17,336
NECK AND NECK?

166
00:07:17,403 --> 00:07:18,404
He's going easy on me.

167
00:07:18,471 --> 00:07:20,907
-Wait.
-He's putting on an act.

168
00:07:21,474 --> 00:07:22,542
BUT

169
00:07:25,378 --> 00:07:26,512
DID THE MARINE DELIVER?

170
00:07:26,579 --> 00:07:28,014
-What?
-Really?

171
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:31,184
SLAM

172
00:07:34,587 --> 00:07:35,588
-That's…
-How awful.

173
00:07:35,655 --> 00:07:38,624
-That's more humiliating.
-That hurts him even more.

174
00:07:38,691 --> 00:07:41,494
-You've humiliated him.
-Just end it. Why did you do that?

175
00:07:41,561 --> 00:07:42,728
Salute!

176
00:07:42,795 --> 00:07:43,863
Don't cry, Kang-rok!

177
00:07:43,930 --> 00:07:45,498
Why did you kill him twice?

178
00:07:45,565 --> 00:07:46,966
-He's crying!
-Why did you kill him twice?

179
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,335
-All right, let's do this.
-I'm sorry.

180
00:07:49,402 --> 00:07:51,370
Let him take five before we resume.

181
00:07:51,437 --> 00:07:54,106
HE GETS THE 5-MINUTE BREAK PERK

182
00:07:54,173 --> 00:07:58,411
-All four of them lost.
-That only leaves Hyun-suk.

183
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:00,480
-I've lost a lot of strength.
-Just come.

184
00:08:00,546 --> 00:08:02,448
Please show us.
He'll do well after saying that.

185
00:08:02,515 --> 00:08:03,616
My knees hurt.

186
00:08:03,683 --> 00:08:05,284
-He's here.
-Come on.

187
00:08:05,351 --> 00:08:07,253
-I'm really weak.
-You're really tall.

188
00:08:07,320 --> 00:08:10,256
Hyun-suk is our last hope.

189
00:08:18,631 --> 00:08:20,166
DANGLING

190
00:08:25,638 --> 00:08:27,306
CHEF FROZEN SHOULDERS,
CHOI HYUN-SUK WINS!

191
00:08:27,373 --> 00:08:28,574
He let me win.

192
00:08:30,610 --> 00:08:32,778
Choi Hyun-suk!

193
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:35,882
-Choi Hyun-suk wins!
-No way!

194
00:08:35,948 --> 00:08:38,351
I KNEW HE COULD DO IT

195
00:08:38,417 --> 00:08:40,353
Choi Hyun-suk!

196
00:08:40,419 --> 00:08:41,888
HYUN-SUK SAVED THE SHOW'S PRIDE

197
00:08:41,954 --> 00:08:43,789
No way. What was that?

198
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:44,991
-No way.
-That was good.

199
00:08:45,057 --> 00:08:46,893
-Did you go easy on him? No, right?
-He went easy on me.

200
00:08:46,959 --> 00:08:48,227
-It was real.
-It was?

201
00:08:48,294 --> 00:08:51,531
Once he toppled my hand over,
I couldn't bring it back up.

202
00:08:53,199 --> 00:08:56,636
He must've lost some energy
because of two previous rounds.

203
00:08:56,702 --> 00:08:58,738
Wait, can we film this again?

204
00:08:58,804 --> 00:09:00,573
Just this part. Let me hold it here.

205
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:01,641
ALL OF A SUDDEN?

206
00:09:02,842 --> 00:09:04,977
LEAVING

207
00:09:06,512 --> 00:09:07,513
GASP

208
00:09:08,581 --> 00:09:11,484
He left nonchalantly like DEX,
without celebrating.

209
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:13,286
Man, that killed my pride.

210
00:09:13,352 --> 00:09:15,288
So this is how everyone felt.

211
00:09:15,354 --> 00:09:17,123
-Gosh.
-That was it.

212
00:09:17,189 --> 00:09:19,559
He showed that to DEX.

213
00:09:19,625 --> 00:09:22,929
Please give him a hand.
It wasn't easy to do that.

214
00:09:22,995 --> 00:09:26,632
And now,
let's turn DEX's fridge inside out!

215
00:09:26,699 --> 00:09:28,668
WHAT'S IN DEX'S FRIDGE?

216
00:09:29,535 --> 00:09:33,039
The hottest single man as of right now.

217
00:09:33,105 --> 00:09:36,242
It's time to rummage through DEX's fridge.

218
00:09:36,309 --> 00:09:38,811
-Where are you from?
-I'm originally from Suncheon.

219
00:09:38,878 --> 00:09:39,979
-Suncheon.
-Yes.

220
00:09:40,046 --> 00:09:43,082
-He'd have ingredients he got from there.
-Of course.

221
00:09:43,149 --> 00:09:46,519
Let's go through his fridge
like we're checking his military locker.

222
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,087
That sounds great.

223
00:09:48,154 --> 00:09:50,122
Let's find out how he's living.

224
00:09:50,189 --> 00:09:53,826
-We present DEX's fridge!
-DEX's fridge!

225
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:55,661
EXCLAIMING

226
00:09:55,728 --> 00:09:58,698
DID SOMETHING SURPRISE THEM?

227
00:09:59,899 --> 00:10:02,001
We should salute the fridge.

228
00:10:02,068 --> 00:10:03,836
-Is this your military locker?
-Let's salute.

229
00:10:03,903 --> 00:10:05,972
HIS NEATLY ORGANIZED FRIDGE
CALLS FOR A SALUTE

230
00:10:06,038 --> 00:10:07,940
These are organized by colors and types.

231
00:10:08,007 --> 00:10:12,011
-It's like a convenience store.
-It's like the morning assembly.

232
00:10:12,078 --> 00:10:14,880
-The beverage fridge.
-They're in good discipline.

233
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:19,151
These are usually at a convenience store
to load new beverages.

234
00:10:19,218 --> 00:10:20,486
It's so convenient.

235
00:10:20,553 --> 00:10:24,390
I need at least two cans of beverages
whenever I eat a meal.

236
00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:26,626
And I got that
because I consume a lot of beverages,

237
00:10:26,692 --> 00:10:28,461
and it wasn't easy to keep it organized.

238
00:10:28,527 --> 00:10:32,832
Look at these.
I mean, one of them could look this way.

239
00:10:32,898 --> 00:10:36,502
-They're all looking forward.
-Their labels show.

240
00:10:36,569 --> 00:10:40,606
And of course, this one.
He's different from that family.

241
00:10:40,673 --> 00:10:44,377
Look at this.
She had all those kimchi from Anseong.

242
00:10:44,443 --> 00:10:46,412
We can find these at stores.

243
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:48,648
-I feel small.
-It's okay.

244
00:10:48,714 --> 00:10:50,983
-Do you also like eggs?
-Yes.

245
00:10:51,050 --> 00:10:55,454
I cook eight eggs at a time
when I eat it as a side dish.

246
00:10:55,955 --> 00:10:56,956
-That many?
-Eight?

247
00:10:57,023 --> 00:10:58,024
-Yes.
-Eight?

248
00:10:58,090 --> 00:11:00,860
I never get full when I eat eggs.

249
00:11:00,926 --> 00:11:02,662
It also makes for a nice drinking snack.

250
00:11:02,728 --> 00:11:04,964
-It is. It's great with soju.
-It's nice to eat eggs.

251
00:11:05,031 --> 00:11:06,032
EGGS GO WELL WITH SOJU

252
00:11:06,599 --> 00:11:08,634
Let's look at his vegetable shelf.

253
00:11:08,701 --> 00:11:11,871
Lettuce, perilla leaf, and potatoes.
The end.

254
00:11:11,937 --> 00:11:13,339
Do you not enjoy vegetables?

255
00:11:13,406 --> 00:11:16,475
I only keep the things I like to eat.

256
00:11:16,542 --> 00:11:18,010
I see. Just these three.

257
00:11:18,077 --> 00:11:21,580
I honestly don't like
vegetables like bell pepper and paprika.

258
00:11:21,647 --> 00:11:24,950
And next, Kimchi Fine Da-heening.

259
00:11:25,785 --> 00:11:28,287
-You picked out the vegetables.
-I did.

260
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:31,257
-How did you do that?
-Are you picking on food?

261
00:11:31,323 --> 00:11:34,393
I didn't think
zucchinis would play a big role.

262
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:35,828
SAD ZUCCHINIS

263
00:11:35,895 --> 00:11:38,197
-I have a palate of a child.
-All right.

264
00:11:38,264 --> 00:11:43,536
I recently ate with him
at <i>Single's Inferno</i> team dinner.

265
00:11:43,602 --> 00:11:46,338
He asked to leave out the cucumbers
when he ordered <i>naengmyeon.</i>

266
00:11:46,405 --> 00:11:47,907
-He doesn't eat cucumbers.
-No cucumbers?

267
00:11:47,973 --> 00:11:50,342
-That's right. I can't eat cucumbers.
-Cucumbers?

268
00:11:50,409 --> 00:11:53,813
It has a strong smell,
so I could never eat it since I was young.

269
00:11:53,879 --> 00:11:56,182
So you can't eat cucumbers.
What else can't you eat?

270
00:11:56,248 --> 00:12:00,219
Cucumber, carrot, cilantro,
bell pepper, and more.

271
00:12:00,286 --> 00:12:01,721
But perilla leaves are also fragrant.

272
00:12:01,787 --> 00:12:03,456
I like that smell.

273
00:12:04,156 --> 00:12:05,658
-I see.
-He likes perilla leaves, though.

274
00:12:05,725 --> 00:12:07,093
-Jeez.
-He's picky.

275
00:12:07,159 --> 00:12:10,763
Cilantro tastes like a barbershop.

276
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:13,265
-I agree with you.
-It tastes like a barbershop?

277
00:12:13,332 --> 00:12:14,734
-Barbershop?
-It tastes like a barbershop.

278
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:16,168
What kind of taste is that?

279
00:12:16,235 --> 00:12:19,371
It makes you feel like you're there
once it's in your mouth. I hate it.

280
00:12:19,438 --> 00:12:21,674
I like potatoes but not sweet potatoes.

281
00:12:21,741 --> 00:12:23,809
-You like potatoes but not sweet potatoes?
-No.

282
00:12:23,876 --> 00:12:27,880
I don't like it when sweet potatoes
are made into a dish.

283
00:12:27,947 --> 00:12:30,449
And next. What are these?

284
00:12:30,516 --> 00:12:34,420
-Those are good with yogurt.
-They're called chocolate loops.

285
00:12:34,487 --> 00:12:37,356
I eat that with cereal and milk,

286
00:12:37,423 --> 00:12:39,859
-and even with yogurt. Greek yogurt.
-Those are good.

287
00:12:40,526 --> 00:12:43,562
This fridge has kimchi too.

288
00:12:43,629 --> 00:12:46,732
-Come on. We said that for no reason.
-There is kimchi.

289
00:12:46,799 --> 00:12:48,768
-You have kimchi.
-That's kimchi?

290
00:12:48,834 --> 00:12:51,570
-Why is it in a trash bag?
-Is that a trash bag?

291
00:12:51,637 --> 00:12:53,072
It's a trash bag.

292
00:12:53,139 --> 00:12:55,441
He put it in a trash bag.

293
00:12:55,508 --> 00:12:58,110
-My gosh.
-It's really kimchi.

294
00:12:58,177 --> 00:12:59,545
-This is good quality kimchi.
-It's not trash, is it?

295
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:01,380
There's a story behind this.

296
00:13:01,447 --> 00:13:03,382
I have no idea where I got that from.

297
00:13:03,449 --> 00:13:04,650
-What?
-What?

298
00:13:04,717 --> 00:13:06,552
I got drunk and fell asleep,

299
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:09,255
and I found that in my fridge
the next day.

300
00:13:09,321 --> 00:13:10,990
It was in this trash bag.

301
00:13:11,056 --> 00:13:12,925
-Just like this?
-This wasn't mine.

302
00:13:12,992 --> 00:13:15,995
-It's not even from my neighborhood.
-You're right.

303
00:13:16,061 --> 00:13:18,397
You got this from Yongsan-gu.

304
00:13:18,464 --> 00:13:21,300
Viewers, please reach out
if you have any information.

305
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:26,305
-Let us know if you gave this to him.
-Yes, I have a feeling…

306
00:13:26,372 --> 00:13:30,810
I don't think it's homemade.
Look at the way it's tied.

307
00:13:30,876 --> 00:13:33,345
It looks like it's from
a legitimate place.

308
00:13:33,412 --> 00:13:35,181
-Like a kimchi store or something.
-You're right.

309
00:13:35,247 --> 00:13:37,883
-I think it's radish kimchi.
-DEX, isn't that from Jin-kyung?

310
00:13:37,950 --> 00:13:38,951
Maybe.

311
00:13:39,018 --> 00:13:42,621
-But she doesn't live in Yongsan.
-Does she live in Yongsan?

312
00:13:42,688 --> 00:13:44,857
I don't know about that trash bag.

313
00:13:44,924 --> 00:13:46,458
Did she give it to you in that bag?

314
00:13:47,026 --> 00:13:50,029
-I wouldn't think so.
-No.

315
00:13:50,095 --> 00:13:54,433
She sent us her kimchi before, right?
And it looks just like that.

316
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:55,901
That might be it then.

317
00:13:55,968 --> 00:13:57,670
The best way to find out is

318
00:13:57,736 --> 00:14:00,139
for Jin-kyung to come as our guest.

319
00:14:00,206 --> 00:14:03,843
-You're right.
-When she comes, we can ask if it was her.

320
00:14:03,909 --> 00:14:05,578
-We'll have an answer then.
-Yes.

321
00:14:05,644 --> 00:14:07,646
You have a lot of condiments.

322
00:14:07,713 --> 00:14:10,716
-You have two of the same kind.
-Yes.

323
00:14:10,783 --> 00:14:14,086
-And these. Mustard.
-Yes.

324
00:14:14,153 --> 00:14:18,123
I eat a lot of sauce,
so I run out really quickly.

325
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:20,259
-That's why I need two.
-You stock up.

326
00:14:20,326 --> 00:14:22,094
There's this special sauce I made.

327
00:14:22,161 --> 00:14:24,697
I didn't even want to share the recipe.

328
00:14:24,763 --> 00:14:27,433
I somehow ended up making that sauce,
and it was so good.

329
00:14:27,499 --> 00:14:31,337
Mix sriracha and mustard
in the same ratio.

330
00:14:31,403 --> 00:14:32,538
The same ratio?

331
00:14:32,605 --> 00:14:34,073
It kind of looks like <i>ssamjang</i>.

332
00:14:34,907 --> 00:14:38,277
-It's strong, so try just a little bit.
-Try some.

333
00:14:38,344 --> 00:14:39,745
DEX'S SECRET SAUCE,
WHAT'S IT LIKE?

334
00:14:44,216 --> 00:14:45,517
SPICY

335
00:14:46,085 --> 00:14:48,420
DOES IT TASTE INTENSE?

336
00:14:48,921 --> 00:14:50,890
FEELING DIZZY

337
00:14:52,157 --> 00:14:55,094
-Is it spicy?
-It's quite pungent,

338
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:56,528
but I get why he likes it.

339
00:14:56,595 --> 00:14:58,564
-It'll taste good with meat.
-Right.

340
00:14:58,631 --> 00:15:00,466
It goes well with shrimp too.

341
00:15:00,532 --> 00:15:04,336
-This is the kind of flavor he likes.
-All right.

342
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:08,641
What are these? You have so many of them.
Two, four, six, eight, ten. Ten bottles.

343
00:15:08,707 --> 00:15:11,043
-Strawberry jam.
-It says strawberry.

344
00:15:11,110 --> 00:15:13,078
I have butter back there.

345
00:15:13,145 --> 00:15:15,180
I bought those for my odd taste in food.

346
00:15:15,247 --> 00:15:17,950
For instance, I like in-flight meals.

347
00:15:18,784 --> 00:15:19,785
On flights?

348
00:15:19,852 --> 00:15:24,256
When you're on a flight, you get bread,
butter, and jam as an appetizer.

349
00:15:24,323 --> 00:15:25,324
Yes, on bread.

350
00:15:25,391 --> 00:15:29,161
I like that so much
and crave it at home from time to time.

351
00:15:29,228 --> 00:15:31,430
He's just like me. Whenever I see a plane,

352
00:15:31,497 --> 00:15:33,632
-I go, "I want an in-flight meal."
-Me too!

353
00:15:33,699 --> 00:15:35,634
-Really?
-There are people like them.

354
00:15:35,701 --> 00:15:39,571
I always make sure I eat the meal
no matter how sleepy I am.

355
00:15:39,638 --> 00:15:41,573
-The bread they give is delicious.
-There's that taste.

356
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:43,943
-It's good.
-There's fun in in-flight meals.

357
00:15:44,009 --> 00:15:46,312
That soju bottle back there

358
00:15:46,378 --> 00:15:50,916
is sesame oil sent by my grandmother
from back home, pressed at a mill.

359
00:15:50,983 --> 00:15:52,351
-Sesame oil.
-Right.

360
00:15:52,418 --> 00:15:55,187
Let's move on to the freezer.

361
00:15:55,254 --> 00:15:57,556
-I see some shrimp.
-Shrimp.

362
00:15:57,623 --> 00:15:58,624
Do you like shrimp?

363
00:15:58,691 --> 00:16:01,327
-One bag only has the heads.
-This one only has shrimp heads.

364
00:16:01,393 --> 00:16:03,429
When I cleaned the shrimp,

365
00:16:03,495 --> 00:16:07,499
I separated them
to stir-fry them in butter.

366
00:16:07,566 --> 00:16:09,301
-Fried shrimp heads are a good snack.
-Yes.

367
00:16:09,368 --> 00:16:12,471
Like a drinking snack. But I haven't had
the chance to make it yet.

368
00:16:12,538 --> 00:16:14,974
And of course, some meat.

369
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:17,509
-I love meat.
-I see.

370
00:16:18,277 --> 00:16:19,878
I go through the packs very quickly.

371
00:16:19,945 --> 00:16:21,246
Is that so?

372
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:23,849
These are… Is this just lard?

373
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:29,254
My mom makes kimchi <i>jjigae</i>
with lots of fat on the pork.

374
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:32,591
So I cook it with those
whenever I miss that flavor.

375
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:35,361
Do you only eat drumsticks?
I only see chicken drumsticks.

376
00:16:35,427 --> 00:16:37,730
Yes, I don't like chicken breast.

377
00:16:37,796 --> 00:16:40,866
-I hate dry meat.
-I see.

378
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:43,602
-I make spicy braised chicken with those.
-Spicy braised chicken.

379
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:45,604
-I see.
-You must cook often.

380
00:16:45,671 --> 00:16:47,606
These must be clams.

381
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:50,175
-Yes, those are…
-Why do you have so much?

382
00:16:50,242 --> 00:16:52,277
-Those are called surf clams.
-Surf clams.

383
00:16:52,344 --> 00:16:56,949
I collected those myself
when I was on <i>Fresh off the Sea</i>.

384
00:16:57,016 --> 00:16:58,984
-Surf clams are delicious.
-They are.

385
00:16:59,051 --> 00:17:02,054
My, you have four bags of these.

386
00:17:02,121 --> 00:17:03,789
-I collected a lot.
-I see.

387
00:17:03,856 --> 00:17:06,091
And these.

388
00:17:06,158 --> 00:17:08,894
-Those are for my in-flight meals.
-In-flight meals?

389
00:17:08,961 --> 00:17:11,030
-For in-flight meals.
-In-flight meals?

390
00:17:11,096 --> 00:17:13,031
-I eat those with jam and butter.
-Yes.

391
00:17:13,098 --> 00:17:16,001
-You have this bread too.
-Croissant with jam and butter.

392
00:17:16,068 --> 00:17:18,270
HE'S SERIOUS
ABOUT IN-FLIGHT MEALS

393
00:17:18,337 --> 00:17:21,473
And room temperature ingredients.

394
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:23,876
-Sweet corn soup.
-For my in-flight meals.

395
00:17:23,942 --> 00:17:26,645
-In-flight meals.
-He's serious.

396
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:27,946
You have these everywhere.

397
00:17:28,013 --> 00:17:31,216
I even bought a cup
to make that small amount.

398
00:17:31,283 --> 00:17:33,218
He's living his dream.

399
00:17:33,285 --> 00:17:36,555
It's been a while since I've flown,
so I've been missing it.

400
00:17:36,622 --> 00:17:39,191
That was all for DEX's fridge.

401
00:17:39,258 --> 00:17:41,093
HIS FRIDGE WAS FULL OF CHARACTER

402
00:17:41,994 --> 00:17:44,463
And now, let us find out

403
00:17:44,530 --> 00:17:48,867
what DEX's orders are and which
of the four contenders will fulfill them.

404
00:17:48,934 --> 00:17:51,170
Here are DEX's orders.

405
00:17:52,971 --> 00:17:56,341
"Amazing Jeolla-style full-course meal."

406
00:17:56,408 --> 00:17:59,011
-"Amazing."
-"Amazing."

407
00:17:59,078 --> 00:18:02,848
I wanted an amazing
Jeolla-style full-course meal.

408
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:06,051
My hometown is Suncheon,
South Jeolla Province,

409
00:18:06,118 --> 00:18:08,620
and I now live alone away from my parents.

410
00:18:08,687 --> 00:18:12,591
And honestly, the food in Seoul
is bland for my liking.

411
00:18:12,658 --> 00:18:16,662
I don't know if I have enough ingredients,
but I want to experience

412
00:18:16,728 --> 00:18:17,729
that savory, bold,

413
00:18:17,796 --> 00:18:20,699
and strong-flavored dishes
you can find in my hometown.

414
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,167
Very well.

415
00:18:22,234 --> 00:18:24,536
Show us the second order.

416
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:28,440
-"<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Air in-flight meal."
-"<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> Air in-flight meal."

417
00:18:28,507 --> 00:18:32,177
-He kept talking about it.
-I knew he'd ask for that.

418
00:18:32,244 --> 00:18:33,979
I'm an in-flight meal enthusiast,

419
00:18:34,046 --> 00:18:39,184
and I believe there are chefs
who specialize in Western cuisine.

420
00:18:39,251 --> 00:18:44,156
Let us begin the 15-minute cook-off
with ingredients from DEX's fridge!

421
00:18:44,223 --> 00:18:48,460
We'll start the first battle
with DEX's ingredients.

422
00:18:48,527 --> 00:18:51,930
Sam Kim,
the star Italian chef of the show,

423
00:18:51,997 --> 00:18:57,503
is up against Jung Ho-young,
the star Japanese chef of the show.

424
00:18:57,569 --> 00:19:02,741
And the order is titled,
"Amazing Jeolla-style full-course meal."

425
00:19:02,808 --> 00:19:04,643
I'm looking forward to this.

426
00:19:05,410 --> 00:19:08,247
-You're rather good at the dialect.
-Of course.

427
00:19:08,313 --> 00:19:11,483
-I'm looking forward to this.
-Right?

428
00:19:11,550 --> 00:19:13,118
Where are you from?

429
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:15,020
I'm from Yeonhui-dong.

430
00:19:16,688 --> 00:19:19,057
I was born in Seoul,

431
00:19:19,124 --> 00:19:23,162
but my parents are from regions
near your hometown.

432
00:19:23,228 --> 00:19:26,598
My father's hometown is Hwasun,
and my mother's hometown is Damyang.

433
00:19:26,665 --> 00:19:29,601
So I'm confident in cooking up
a good Jeolla-style meal.

434
00:19:29,668 --> 00:19:32,237
-Oh, wow.
-You must know what he's craving.

435
00:19:32,304 --> 00:19:33,572
Hwasun, huh?

436
00:19:33,639 --> 00:19:36,742
There's an amazing story
between these two.

437
00:19:36,808 --> 00:19:39,578
In the previous season,
you two have made Korean cuisine

438
00:19:39,645 --> 00:19:41,380
for Park Chul-min, who said it tasted

439
00:19:41,446 --> 00:19:43,448
-just like his mother's food.
-Just like his mother's food.

440
00:19:43,515 --> 00:19:45,384
This is how we eat it back in my hometown.

441
00:19:45,450 --> 00:19:48,587
Chef Ho-young was able to make it
because he knows the flavor.

442
00:19:48,654 --> 00:19:50,689
-He's from the same region.
-Yes.

443
00:19:50,756 --> 00:19:53,492
-He's moved to tears.
-Yes.

444
00:19:53,559 --> 00:19:55,227
BACK THEN,
CHUL-MIN CHOSE CHEF HO-YOUNG

445
00:19:55,294 --> 00:19:57,329
Chef Jung Ho-young wins!

446
00:19:57,396 --> 00:19:59,665
Chef Ho-young wins!

447
00:19:59,731 --> 00:20:01,466
IT'S AN EPISODE
PEOPLE STILL TALK ABOUT

448
00:20:01,533 --> 00:20:04,002
-Do you remember?
-Yes, it was a battle to remember.

449
00:20:04,069 --> 00:20:05,871
Both Chul-min

450
00:20:05,938 --> 00:20:07,606
and Chef Ho-young were moved to tears.

451
00:20:07,673 --> 00:20:09,608
But Sam couldn't cry.

452
00:20:09,675 --> 00:20:12,844
-He also cried because he lost.
-Because he lost.

453
00:20:12,911 --> 00:20:14,880
-I see.
-He said it was unfair.

454
00:20:14,947 --> 00:20:17,816
Back in the waiting room, he kept asking,

455
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:21,887
"What can I do
to make good kimchi<i> jjigae</i>?"

456
00:20:21,954 --> 00:20:23,889
-About Korean cuisine?
-Yes, about Korean cuisine.

457
00:20:23,956 --> 00:20:26,325
When we travel to Jeolla Province,

458
00:20:26,391 --> 00:20:28,594
we always get a lot of side dishes,

459
00:20:28,660 --> 00:20:30,229
so I hope
they took that into consideration,

460
00:20:30,295 --> 00:20:33,065
although I'm not sure
how many they can make in 15 minutes.

461
00:20:33,131 --> 00:20:35,701
-It's a full-course meal.
-I look forward to it.

462
00:20:36,535 --> 00:20:38,804
CHEF SAM'S INGREDIENTS: PORK FOR JJIGAE,
SRIRACHA, CHICKEN STOCK,

463
00:20:38,870 --> 00:20:41,006
SALTED CUTLASSFISH INNARDS, DRUMSTICKS,
RADISH KIMCHI, SURF CLAMS, AND MORE

464
00:20:41,073 --> 00:20:43,308
CHEF HO-YOUNG'S INGREDIENTS: BONE BROTH,
SALTED CUTLASSFISH INNARDS, SESAME OIL,

465
00:20:43,375 --> 00:20:45,644
DRUMSTICKS, SESAME,
POTATO, OYSTER SAUCE

466
00:20:45,711 --> 00:20:47,913
-Chef Ho-young, what's your dish?
-Yes?

467
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:50,482
My dish is titled…

468
00:20:50,549 --> 00:20:53,852
<i>Pot-Pot-Pot-Pot-lash</i>

469
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:57,422
<i>Pot-Pot-Pot-Pot-lash</i>

470
00:20:57,489 --> 00:21:00,158
-Was that a parody of "Whiplash"?
-Yes, you're right.

471
00:21:00,726 --> 00:21:01,727
AGAIN, HIS DANCE
IS ODDLY CAPTIVATING

472
00:21:01,793 --> 00:21:03,161
"Pot-lash."

473
